==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Processive
<hw>Pro*ces"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Proceeding;
advancing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Because it is language, -- ergo, <qex>processive</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- (Biochemistry) acting from one end of a polymer, and continuing
to act on the same polymer, rather than detaching and re-binding
randomly to other molecules. Said of polymerases or hydrolytic enzymes.
Opposed to "distributive". Colloquially, (laboratory slang) processive
and distributive enzymes may be referred to as "clingers" and "hoppers",
respectively. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Process plate</ent>⟦br⟧
